# Documentation structure

## New Markdown files

- Do **not** create new product/project Markdown at the repository root.
- Create them under `docs/` in the correct domain folder:
  - `docs/architecture/` — system design, domain map
  - `docs/backend/` — FastAPI / API
  - `docs/frontend/` — Admin UI pointers (app README stays in `frontend/`)
  - `docs/database/` — ERD, Alembic, DB rules
  - `docs/deployment/` — install, config, release
  - `docs/development/` — test summaries, change plans
  - `docs/trading/` — ops, paper/live, incidents
  - `docs/ai/` — AI indexes and AI-focused docs
  - `docs/reference/` — roadmaps, inventories, reports
  - `docs/archive/steps/` — STEP work logs only
  - `docs/archive/notes/` — apply notes
  - `docs/archive/obsolete/` — superseded guides (move, do not delete)

## After creating a doc

1. Add a link and one-line description to that folder’s `README.md`.
2. If it is a **current** (non-archive) doc, also link it from `docs/README.md` when it is a primary entry.
3. Prefer relative links; keep the domain tree intact.

## Root exceptions (do not proliferate)

Allowed at repo root only for portal/agent continuity:

- `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `PROJECT_STATUS.md`
- Agent/persona: `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`
- App-local: `frontend/README.md` (and similar package README under `frontend/`)

New how-to, runbook, design, STEP, or checklist docs belong under `docs/…`, not the root.

## Deletion

Do not delete Markdown content without explicit user approval; move superseded docs to `docs/archive/obsolete/` instead.

## Index

Canonical doc map: `docs/README.md`
